                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/11–2144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-21T12:00:00+03:06"
                            >November 21, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>348. Shaikh Yussuf Yassin, Deputy Foreign Minister, informed me confidentially
                    that by order of the King official written notice was <pb facs="0781" n="769"
                        xml:id="pg_769"/> today given to Cable and Wireless reserving the right to
                    modify the existing agreement in such way as His Majesty may decide. Since this
                    was done in compliance with request transmitted in consequence of Department’s
                    234, November 3, 7 p.m. and my several subsequent inquiries I did not deliver
                    message in Department’s 252, November 18, 7 p.m. which I had with me already for
                    delivery. Comment in separate telegram.<note n="4" xml:id="d841fn4">Telegram
                        349, November 21, 1 p.m., <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
